[While this is sad news, I was stuck with the thought that minks need to have some social distance. The virus is believed to spread from close contact and minks are in a facility without much distance between the animals. Perhaps, adding HEPA filters to the air handlers may be helpful?

I am saddened to learn of this event. Saddened for the animals and for the individuals involved who may have encountered the virus.

There is no indication as to how these minks became infected. The question then becomes, was a human caretaker the source of the virus to the minks? Or was the virus within the food, or bedding, or water, or some other source?

The mink fur trade is big business and this is certainly a blow to the producers of this facility as well as the anxiety which surely must be at a high pitch in other facilities. Restricting movement and doing more extensive testing seems an appropriate measure. - Mod.TG

